* B Beta III IV I AXLE (HQ) (EX) (IP) (TR) (BY)
It would be wrong to romanticize.
The Folvilles, the Coterels and their like were tough, brutal and unscrupulous men,
some way removed from their more refined counterparts of the ballads.
Their attacks were particularly directed against the rich;
they specialized in extortion ...
Such victims were probably selected, not from any tender respect for 'social justice',
but rather from a well-judged sense of where the best pickings lay.
